# ============================================================
# UPSTREAM TEMPLATE .gitignore
# ============================================================
# This .gitignore ships with the shared template.
# It ensures that machine-specific data in local/ is committed
# to the machine's own origin but NEVER reaches upstream.
#
# Git remotes:
#   upstream = shared template repo (agents, skills, scripts)
#   origin   = this machine's fork (includes local/)
# ============================================================

# --- Machine-specific (tracked in origin, blocked from upstream) ---
# The local/ directory is committed to this machine's fork.
# To prevent it from reaching upstream, the propose-upstream script
# explicitly excludes it. This .gitignore entry is a safety net
# for anyone who accidentally tries to push local/ to upstream.
# NOTE: Do NOT add local/ here — it must be tracked by git in the fork.

# --- Secrets (NEVER committed anywhere) ---
local/.env
*.key
*.pem
*.p12

# --- Runtime files (NEVER committed) ---
local/logs/
.claude/session-log.jsonl
.claude/changed-files.log
.claude/telegram-offset

# --- OS & Editor ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/
